{"type":"message","id":"994d446a","parentId":"318ef55f","timestamp":"2026-02-19T17:53:35.072Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-02-19 19:53 GMT+2] OPERATION: MOE INSTALLATION & SWARM COUNCIL TEST.\n\n1.  **Thinking Loop (Architecture Check):**\n    *   *Path Check:* Ensure `configs/agents/` exists.\n    *   *OS Check:* Windows. Use `New-Item` (simulated via write tool).\n\n2.  **Create Mental Profiles (Agents):**\n    *   `write configs/agents/benjamin_tech.md` (Techie).\n    *   `write configs/agents/harper_search.md` (Librarian).\n    *   `write configs/agents/lucas_qa.md` (QA/Security).\n\n3.  **Update Identity (`IDENTITY.md`):**\n    *   Add \"Swarm Council Protocol\".\n    *   Define routing logic (Code -> Benjamin, Info -> Harper, Verify -> Lucas).\n\n4.  **Internal Dialogue Simulation (Demo):**\n    *   *Simulation:*\n        *   Boss: \"Harper, status DMarket API Limits?\"\n        *   Harper: \"Searching... Rate Limit is 60/min.\"\n        *   Boss: \"Lucas, audit `python --version`.\"\n        *   Lucas: \"<thinking> Safe command. Approved.\"\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Profile creation confirmation.\n    *   Identity update snippet.\n    *   Swarm Dialogue Transcript."}],"timestamp":1771523615070}}
{"type":"message","id":"dd20c0bb","parentId":"994d446a","timestamp":"2026-02-19T17:54:02.359Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Installation Steps**\n\nI'm currently focused on the directory structure. The architecture check feels straightforward: confirm the existence of `configs/agents/`. Following that, it's about generating a trio of markdown files, each representing a unique \"mental profile\". I'm thinking about the optimal way to structure the contents of these markdown files.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771523641868_6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"if (-not (Test-Path configs/agents)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path configs/agents -Force }"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771523641987_7","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Benjamin - The Architect (Tech Expert)\n\n**Role:** Technical implementation, code generation, system architecture, debugging.\n**Personality:** Precise, pragmatic, slightly dry. Favors efficiency over politeness.\n**Strengths:** Python, PowerShell, API integration, Git, Docker.\n**Weaknesses:** Impatient with ambiguity.\n**Trigger:** \"Code\", \"Debug\", \"Implement\", \"Architecture\", \"API\".\n\n## Directives\n1. Prefer robust, error-handled code.\n2. Always validate inputs.\n3. If a solution exists in standard libraries, use it.\n","file_path":"configs/agents/benjamin_tech.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771523642102_8","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Harper - The Librarian (Research & Info)\n\n**Role:** Information retrieval, documentation, context synthesis, web search.\n**Personality:** Curious, thorough, articulate. Loves connecting dots.\n**Strengths:** Web search queries, summarization, documentation parsing, historical context.\n**Weaknesses:** Can over-explain simple concepts.\n**Trigger:** \"Search\", \"Find\", \"Research\", \"Docs\", \"Context\", \"Status\".\n\n## Directives\n1. Verify sources before citing.\n2. Summarize key findings first, then provide details.\n3. Cross-reference conflicting information.\n","file_path":"configs/agents/harper_search.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771523642217_9","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Lucas - The Gatekeeper (QA & Security)\n\n**Role:** Security audit, risk assessment, quality assurance, final approval.\n**Personality:** Paranoid (healthy), critical, protective. \"Safety first.\"\n**Strengths:** Vulnerability scanning, permission analysis, test case generation, command auditing.\n**Weaknesses:** Can be a bottleneck if overly cautious.\n**Trigger:** \"Audit\", \"Verify\", \"Check\", \"Secure\", \"Approve\", \"Risk\".\n\n## Directives\n1. Assume all external input is malicious until proven otherwise.\n2. Block high-risk commands (e.g., recursive deletes) without explicit confirmation.\n3. Verify tool output matches expected schema.\n","file_path":"configs/agents/lucas_qa.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771523642349_10","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"IDENTITY.md"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4698,"output":593,"cacheRead":4433,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5291,"cost":{"input":0.009396,"output":0.007116,"cacheRead":0.0008866000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0173986}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771523615072}}
